  "text": "Prometheus implements web UI authentication through three primary mechanisms:\n\n1. **BasicAuth Middleware**: The authentication is configured via a web configuration file specified by the `--web.config.file` flag (cmd/prometheus/main.go:401-404). The configuration file path is passed to the HTTP server initialization and handled by the toolkit_web.ServeMultiple() function (web/web.go:760), which is part of the exporter-toolkit dependency. This middleware provides BasicAuth support with bcrypt password hashing.\n\n2. **TLS Client Certificate Validation**: The same web configuration file also supports TLS client certificate validation through the `client_auth_type` and `client_ca_file` configuration options, as documented in docs/configuration/https.md. The toolkit_web.ServeMultiple() function in web/web.go:760 processes these TLS settings during HTTP server setup.\n\n3. **Admin API Access Control**: The admin API endpoints for TSDB operations (delete_series, clean_tombstones, snapshot) are protected by checking the `enableAdmin` flag in their handler functions. These endpoints are:\n   - `deleteSeries()` (web/api/v1/api.go:2026-2057): Checks if api.enableAdmin is false, returns error \"admin APIs disabled\"\n   - `snapshot()` (web/api/v1/api.go:2059-2091): Checks if api.enableAdmin is false, returns error \"admin APIs disabled\"\n   - `cleanTombstones()` (web/api/v1/api.go:2093-2102): Checks if api.enableAdmin is false, returns error \"admin APIs disabled\"\n\nThe enableAdmin flag is controlled by the `--web.enable-admin-api` command-line flag (cmd/prometheus/main.go:430-431), which defaults to false.\n\nThe authentication flow works as follows:\n1. Command-line flags are parsed in cmd/prometheus/main.go, capturing the web.config.file path and web.enable-admin-api setting\n2. A web.Handler is created via web.New() (web/web.go:318-607), which registers API routes\n3. The handler.Run() method (web/web.go:722-770) is called with the webConfig path\n4. Inside Run(), toolkit_web.ServeMultiple() is invoked with the FlagConfig containing the web configuration file path (web/web.go:760)\n5. The exporter-toolkit middleware handles BasicAuth and TLS certificate validation at the HTTP server level\n6. Admin API endpoints in web/api/v1/api.go check the enableAdmin flag before allowing operations"
}

